"{\n  \"text\": \"Hi everybody, I want to talk about why using earthworms and microbes and all the natural things that you find in life as opposed to tilling work much more effectively. And this is because when a root uh bores into it, tills the ground and then dies, the microbes will use that organic matter of the root and incorporate that. When the earthworms pass through it, they pass earthworm castings behind them. When you use a tiller, you basically create space and then leave a space when the tilling fork leaves. And what this does is that you as soon as the rain comes, it just further compacts it. So you fluff it up, but only temporarily, the net result is a more compacted soil. And when you do it organically, the net effect is a more fluffy soil. Anyway, thanks y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hi everybody, I want to talk about why using earthworms and microbes and all the natural things that you find in life as opposed to tilling work much more effectively.\",\n      \"start\": 1.36,\n      \"end\": 10.56,\n      \"duration\": 9.2,\n      \"confidence\": 0.996,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" Hi\",\n          \"start\": 1.36,\n          \"end\": 1.68,\n          \"duration\": 0.32,\n          \"confidence\": 0.997\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 1.84,\n          \"end\": 2.0,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 2.0,\n          \"end\": 2.24,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"start\": 2.24,\n          \"end\": 2.32,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \",\",\n          \"start\": 2.32,\n          \"end\": 2.48,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.913\n        },\n        {\n         